{"lemma":"رَبْطُ","slug":"رَبْطُ","root":"ر.ب.ط","root_slug":"ر-ب-ط","root_link":"/words/roots/ر-ب-ط","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"رَبْطُ","root":"ربط","pos":"V","occurrence_count":3},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":8},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n14506"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B1%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%92%D8%B7%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to tie up, to bind","examples":[{"text":"رَبَطَ الرَّجُلُ حِذَاءَهُ بِإحكَامِ.","english":"The man tied his shoes tightly."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to fasten, to attach"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to strengthen (used with the word for \"heart\" قَلْب (qalb))","examples":[{"text":"وَرَبَطْنَا عَلَىٰ قُلُوبِهِمْ إِذْ قَامُوا فَقَالُوا رَبُّنَا رَبُّ السَّمَاوَاتِ وَالْأَرْضِ","english":"And We strengthened their hearts when they stood up and declared, “Our Lord is the Lord of the heavens and the earth."},{"text":"لَوْلَا أَن رَّبَطْنَا عَلَىٰ قَلْبِهَا لِتَكُونَ مِنَ الْمُؤْمِنِينَ","english":"had We not reassured her heart in order for her to have faith ˹in Allah’s promise˺."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of رَبَطَ (rabaṭa) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"binding"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"fastening"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"tying"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of رَبْطَة (rabṭa)","tags":["form-of","plural"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n14506","headword_ar":"رَبَطَ","root":"rbT","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, &c.,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raboTN","text_ar":"رَبْطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He tied, bound,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made fast,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb, K,) a thing, (S, Msb, * K, * TA,) and a beast; (Mgh, TA;) and in like manner ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ArtbT","text_ar":"ارتبط","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he tied,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bound,"},{"kind":"text","text":"a beast"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with a rope, in order that he might not run away."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ka*aA raA^osFA mina Ald~awaAb~i","text_ar":"كَذَا رَاْسًا مِنَ الدَّوَابِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN yarotabiTu","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ يَرْتَبِطُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one ties so many head of beasts:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the verb may here have a different signification, explained below]. (S, TA.) And it is said in a prov.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aisotakoramota faA@robiTo","text_ar":"اِسْتَكْرَمْتَ فَا@رْبِطْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or, accord. to one relation,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akoramota","text_ar":"اَكْرَمْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thou hast found a generous horse, therefore do thou preserve him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, as some relate it, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faA@rotabiTo","text_ar":"فَا@رْتَبِطْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": relating to the duty of preservation. (TA.) See also 3. ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabaTa Ealayohi","text_ar":"رَبَطَ عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He held back,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"drew back, from him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as though he confined, and bound, himself. (TA, from a trad.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabaTa jaA^o$uhu","text_ar":"رَبَطَ جَاْشُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ribaATapN","text_ar":"رِبَاطَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His heart became strong, and firm, and resolute,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, * TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so that he did not flee on the occasion of fear."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA. [In the CK,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabaTa jaA^o$ahu","text_ar":"رَبَطَ جَاْشَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which would be more properly rendered (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He strengthened,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fortified, his heart."},{"kind":"text","text":"]) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabaTa li*`lika AlA^amori jaA^o$FA","text_ar":"رَبَطَ لِذٰلِكَ الاَمْرِ جَاْشًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He constrained himself to be patient, and confined,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"restricted, himself to that thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affair."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabaTa A@ll~`hu EalaY qalobihi","text_ar":"رَبَطَ ا@للّٰهُ عَلَى قَلْبِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biAlS~abori","text_ar":"بِالصَّبْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God inspired him with patience."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K.) Thus in the Kur [xviii. 13],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"warabaTonaA EalaY quluwbihimo","text_ar":"وَرَبَطْنَا عَلَى قُلُوبِهِمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And we inspired them with patience:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strengthened them with patience."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd.) And in like manner in [viii. 11 and] xxviii. 9. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","TA","Mgh"]}]}}